reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My baby has NEVER HAD A RASH AFTER 14 months
reviews.reviewText: I HAVE USED THESE FOR MY OWN PERSONAL EMERGENCY. i was out of sanitary pads and had no choice, but let me tell you if they had the option to purchase them as pads I would. I've NEVER felt anything as soft and soothing as these diapers. I have a problem with general pads and have to look for all cotton ones because I always get irritation. These worked so well for me I couldn't believe it. Now for my baby's reveiw lol she has NEVER had a rash, thats a blessing because my sweet son who is now 9 years old didn't get to have the best diaper experience and had bad rashes. I know it's 100% the product's fault because even I get a rash when I use certain brands. I agree with some of the reviews regarding the shipment and wait time I've also had to order more than I need so I'm okay for a couple of months but I dont mind that.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: When looking for a diaper for my son, it was important to me to find a brand that was absorbent, hypoallergenic and as non-toxic as possible at an affordable price. Many of the non-toxic diapers I have found during my search are expensive and while I would love to try them, this momma balls on a budget.I have been using the diapers on my baby for a few weeks now and so far there’s been no rash or irritation on my baby. They are absorbent and I have had fewer leaks than other diaper brands I tried like Hello Bello, huggies special delivery and pampers. To be honest, I have yet to find a brand that is completely leak free so fewer leaks works for me.As advertised and like many of the reviews stated, these diapers are extremely soft and velvety to the touch. My favorite part is that they are paraben, phthalate, bleach, fragrance, additive and TCL free!I am very pleased with these diapers!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I used these for baby shower diaper cake
reviews.reviewText: They were perfect for what I needed. I needed to make baby shower cake and these have no designs on them, they will be used for the baby when born.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love how soft these are but aren't good for blowouts
reviews.reviewText: I noticed they absorb slower than other diaper brands. My baby developed a small rash the first time I used these but it went away after using them a couple of times, she has very very sensitive skin so she might've just needed to get used to them. Last week my baby was sick and blew out w/ every one of these diapers. It kept leaking out the sides.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These diapers were the best thing I have found since we canceled our Coterie subscription because it was getting too expensive. They are the same price as Kotori, but the difference is you can buy less at a time so it’s easier to budget. They are extremely soft and absorbent and they don’t cause diaper rash, which is important because my son has the most sensitive skin and struggles with eczema because it’s so dry where we live! Every other diaper we have tried has given him a rash.However…All those good things aside, I highly recommend you try to purchase their diapers directly from their website because we have had nothing but shipment issues through Amazon! It takes a month or longer to arrive so we are constantly having to go to the store and get Millie moon diapers to hold us over until they finally show up! I always try ordering them way in advance, it still took over a month and we had to buy more Millie Moon. One shipment kept getting delayed month after month so I called and canceled and Amazon placed a replacement order. It still has not shipped and it’s been over a week! So I’m just done. What’s the point of ordering diapers if they never actually make it to your house? It’s basically throwing money into the wind and when the diapers decide to show up they show up, while also blowing money on other brands while we are waiting around.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My daughter is extremely sensitive and these are the only diapers that work for her. I use the wipes as well and she is perfectly secure. Her skin is safe and that is all a mother could ask for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My grandson has very sensitive skin and these didn’t irritate his skin and are so soft! They held everything in overnight, no leaks! He wears a size 6 and I was concerned as they didn’t have much extra room to attach the tabs but they stayed put throughout his play and overnight so they have nice strong grip to keep up with his activities. Overall, very pleased! I was surprised the price wasn’t much more than regular brands and since I only have him a few days a month they’ll last for awhile. He’s just starting potty training so I won’t need much more but he will be comfy until then. I highly recommend giving them a try!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024

reviews.reviewText: These diapers are so soft, but don’t let that fool you. They leak out the leg and the top. Incredibly thin. Plan on changing your child’s clothes with each diaper change.

reviews.reviewTitle: Your baby will thank you for this
reviews.reviewText: Softest diapers I have ever tried for my baby. It also lasts longer than regular diapers. I usually use this when I travel with my baby. It's expensive but worth it .
Very soft and well appreciated by the parent I got them for. Sizing is accurate. Little pricey, but worth it if running into diaper rash issues

reviews.reviewTitle: Hypoallergenic, ZERO scent. Absorbent. Comfortable. The softest diaper on the planet!
reviews.reviewText: I reviewed these diapers in different sizes and they have all been the exact same from sizes 1-4. These are the softest diapers you will have ever felt in your life. I will be repeating my previous reviews here as they have been consistent with the quality and everything else thus far:I'm sure you've read it numerous times in other reviews, but I have to repeat it... these diapers are SOOOOO soft. They're basically what I would imagine clouds to feel like if you could actually feel them (lol). They're like pillows for your baby's tush. I cannot express how soft it is. Your baby would thank you for these if they could speak. My baby is just a few days old and not quite big enough for these yet, but I am so eager to put them on her.They feel very high quality, hence why the price might be a bit high. It's currently at $9.99 for a box containing 2 packs of diapers. Each pack has 6 diapers, for a total of 12 diapers. So yes, a little on the pricier side for baby diapers, but keep in mind that you do get what you pay for in this case, 100%. You can see and feel the difference almost immediately.
